<subSubSection id="51C958916F245439D488AD9D336124A1" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2F3A2DF6E301835F1810AE0F090710F5" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="96B8CD48CAA0E0C954FCE9225C1F731F" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Differs from the sympatric 
<taxonomicName id="82C65A00664013BCF71DD8856FBEAE5F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum campaniforme" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="campaniforme">
<emphasis id="014074E6B083CC6E67AE76856D2FFA5C" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Solanum campaniforme</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Roem. &amp; Schultes in its deep forest habitat, leaves with ruffled margins, flowers less than 1 cm in diameter, pedicels with a constriction at the distal end that are swollen in fruit, and few seeds.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
